&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAMHS Specialist Practitioner/ Lead for Mental Health Support Team in schools.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s a refreshing time to join our CAMHS team in Cornwall where your expertise and hard work are recognised with a genuine commitment to your learning and career development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are dedicated to building a compassionate workplace where quality improvement is at the heart of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here’s what we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A supportive management structure, dynamic MDT and excellence working relationships with our commissioners and partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership training up to masters level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Close working with the south west collaborative to share ideas and build networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated quality lead and opportunities for research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may have a RMN or management background with a passion for leading a team that provides high quality care to children and young people,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would love to have an informal conversation with you and please come and visit us in beautiful Cornwall which is a fantastic place to live and work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Find out more and contact Lucy Hayes, Operations Manager by phone on 07554 112 944 or by email at lucy.hayes1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful applicants will be required to prepare a 10 minute presentation on &#39;Developing a MHST Service - opportunities and challenges&#39; before the interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
